            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1945-10-06T07:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1945-10-06T07:00:00-05:00" n="1046" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1046">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.111/10–645: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in China</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Robertson</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Chungking</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1945-10-06T19:00:00+07:00">October 6, 1945—7 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received October 6—2:25 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1748. Upon receipt Dept’s 1558, Sept. 26, we took matter up with Foreign Office.
                    We have now been informed by Foreign Office that instructions are being
                    telegraphed to Chinese Embassy, Washington, to effect that in cases of American
                    civilians with legitimate business in China visas may be issued by appropriate
                    Chinese officials in U. S. without prior reference to Foreign Office for
                        approval.<note n="39" xml:id="d1046fn39">On October 9 an officer of the
                        Chinese Embassy informed the Department that this instruction had been
                        received and also that authorization had been received to issue visas to
                        employees of the Shanghai Power Company who had previously made applications
                        (893.111/10–645).</note>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Robertson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
